Contagious bovine pleuropneumonia - Zambia 19970602.1136
Contagious bovine pleuropneumonia - Zambia (02) 19970927.2038
Date: 13 Jul 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Africa News Service, 13 Jul 2001 [edited

Cattle Disease Breaks Out in Western Province
---------------------------------------------
Contagious bovine pleuropneumonia (CBPP) has broken out in Western
Province, chief veterinary officer in the Ministry of Agriculture, Food and
Fisheries (MAFF) Dominic Minyoi confirmed.
The government has advised all cattle dealers to get permits for any
livestock movement in the area. Dr. Minyoi said new cases of CBPP have been
recorded in Yuka village, 5 km from Kalabo district. He said there were
traces of the disease in Sikongo prior to the partial lift of the ban last
May which spread to Yuka.
Dr. Minyoi attributed the outbreak to possible illegal livestock movements.
He said the partial lift of the ban by the ministry was in response to
cries from the people in Western Province that there were beef shortages
due to high prices.
The ministry advised farmers and cattle dealers in the area to cooperate
with veterinary staff, who will advise them on other options to reduce
further spread.
­­
