[This highly contagious pneumonia is generally accompanied by pleurisy. The
causal organism is _Mycoplasma mycoides mycoides_ small colony type.
Susceptible cattle become infected by inhaling droplets disseminated by
coughing of affected cattle.
Goats and sheep are not important in the epidemiology.
Septicemia produces lesions in the kidneys and placenta, which can be
sources of infection. Transplacental infection of the fetus is known to
occur. In the environment, survival of the organism is poor. However, the
incubation period varies from 3-8 weeks.
In susceptible herds there may be 100 percent morbidity, while mortality is
likely to approach 50 percent. In recovered animals, 25 percent may be
carriers. - Mod.TG
